Class BagExtractor

SimpleFeatureExtractor
public class BagExtractor
extends Object
implements SimpleFeatureExtractor


Copyright (c) 2007-2008, Regents of the University of Colorado
All rights reserved. A class for extracting bag-of-words style features. It allows any type of Annotation to serve as the "words", and allows any type of feature extractor to be applied to each of these "words".

Author:
Steven Bethard

BagExtractor

public BagExtractor(String extractorName,
                    Class<? extends Annotation> annotationClass,
                    SimpleFeatureExtractor featureExtractor)
Extracts bag-of-words style features, running a feature extractor over all "word" Annotations within the focus Annotation.

Parameters:
extractorName - A name identifying this extractor, which will be prefixed to the context string of all features extracted.
annotationClass - The class of Annotation representing "words".
featureExtractor - The feature extractor to be applied to each "word".

public List<Feature> extract(JCas jCas,

Description copied from interface: SimpleFeatureExtractor
Some feature extractors will require some specific number of annotations that is greater than one. Such extractors should not implement this interface.

Specified by:
extract in interface SimpleFeatureExtractor
Parameters:
jCas - the current JCas or view of the document.
focusAnnotation - the annotation for which to collect features.
Returns:
a list of features generated by the extractor for the focus annotation.
